en cheap. A few required you to do something very unique and unintuitive, and hence a solution would be unclear.\n\nThe rest of the game you'd spend exploring the locations and completing quests, some of which are optional, but completing them gains you additional weapon choices or pieces of armour. There are a lot of the dialogue sections in the game where you get to make decisions and choose how you respond. Even if a dialogue choice doesn't have any consequences, it still has an alignment with one of the four deities, and acquiring a certain number of deity-aligned choices nets you a skill point to spend in their skill tree.\n\nOverall it's a pretty fun adventure RPG and anyone who likes Greek mythology should give it a try. It does change some of the stories and characters from the myths slightly, but it's still done in a fresh and engaging manner to keep things interesting. I'll recommend this game. It's quite underrated.\n\nI've done a 19-part let's play video series on Youtube of me playing the game with live voice commentary in case you're interested to see more of the game:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tUoAw8WDhqM&index=1&list=PLlpmhqJE5XfrciEZ4vf5BUEchaoBxsqjX\n"}, {"votes_down": 1, "written_during_early_access": false, "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "timestamp_created": 1429118748, "weighted_vote_score": "0.509943", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_funny": 1, "recommendationid": "15388566", "votes_up": 7, "comment_count": "1", "author": {"steamid": "76561197990241420", "num_reviews": 3, "last_played": 1429117950, "num_games_owned": 196, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_forever": 979}, "timestamp_updated": 1429119999, "received_for_free": false, "review": "Bought this game yesterday since my Steam Library lacked controller friendly RPG's. Managed to finish it in about 12h. I'm surprised I never heard much about the game before. It's by no means a great or even good game but it hits the right spot for someone searching for a game \"like G